devdoc.details: The Pool contract exchanges Dai for yDai at a price defined by a specific formula.

addDelegate(address).details: Enable a delegate to act on the behalf of caller

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

burn(uint256).details: Burn liquidity tokens in exchange for dai and yDai. The liquidity provider needs to have called `pool.approve`.

params.tokensBurned: Amount of liquidity tokens being burned.

returns._0: The amount of reserve tokens returned (daiTokens, yDaiTokens).

buyDai(address,address,uint128).details: Buy Dai for yDai The trader needs to have called `yDai.approve`

params.daiOut: Amount of dai being bought that will be deposited in `to` wallet
params.from: Wallet providing the yDai being sold. Must have approved the operator with `pool.addDelegate(operator)`.
params.to: Wallet receiving the dai being bought

returns._0: Amount of yDai that will be taken from `from` wallet

buyDaiPreview(uint128).details: Returns how much yDai would be required to buy `daiOut` dai.

buyYDai(address,address,uint128).details: Buy yDai for dai The trader needs to have called `dai.approve`

params.from: Wallet providing the dai being sold. Must have approved the operator with `pool.addDelegate(operator)`.
params.to: Wallet receiving the yDai being bought
params.yDaiOut: Amount of yDai being bought that will be deposited in `to` wallet

returns._0: Amount of dai that will be taken from `from` wallet

buyYDaiPreview(uint128).details: Returns how much dai would be required to buy `yDaiOut` yDai.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5,05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the value {ERC20} uses, unless {_setupDecimals} is called. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

init(uint128).details: Mint initial liquidity tokens. The liquidity provider needs to have called `dai.approve`

params.daiIn: The initial Dai liquidity to provide.

mint(uint256).details: Mint liquidity tokens in exchange for adding dai and yDai The liquidity provider needs to have called `dai.approve` and `yDai.approve`.

params.daiOffered: Amount of `dai` being invested, an appropriate amount of `yDai` to be invested alongside will be calculated and taken by this function from the caller.

returns._0: The amount of liquidity tokens minted.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

revokeDelegate(address).details: Stop a delegate from acting on the behalf of caller

sellDai(address,address,uint128).details: Sell Dai for yDai The trader needs to have called `dai.approve`

params.daiIn: Amount of dai being sold that will be taken from the user's wallet
params.from: Wallet providing the dai being sold. Must have approved the operator with `pool.addDelegate(operator)`.
params.to: Wallet receiving the yDai being bought

returns._0: Amount of yDai that will be deposited on `to` wallet

sellDaiPreview(uint128).details: Returns how much yDai would be obtained by selling `daiIn` dai

sellYDai(address,address,uint128).details: Sell yDai for Dai The trader needs to have called `yDai.approve`

params.from: Wallet providing the yDai being sold. Must have approved the operator with `pool.addDelegate(operator)`.
params.to: Wallet receiving the dai being bought
params.yDaiIn: Amount of yDai being sold that will be taken from the user's wallet

returns._0: Amount of dai that will be deposited on `to` wallet

sellYDaiPreview(uint128).details: Returns how much dai would be obtained by selling `yDaiIn` yDai.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}; Requirements: - `sender` and `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - `sender` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``sender``'s tokens of at least `amount`.
